title: Georges Seurat A Sunday on La Grande Jatte – 1884 Unmatted Print
description:
Print developed from Georges Seurat’s A Sunday on La Grande Jatte—1884, 1884/86 from The Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Inspired by research in optical and color theory, Seurat juxtaposed tiny dots of colors that, through optical blending, form a single and, Seurat believed, more brilliantly luminous hue in the viewer's eye. 

  • Print Reproduction
  • Image size:  8.375 x 12.5 in.
  • Full poster size: 11 x 14 in.
  • Material: Premium Cardstock
